01:27:02,619 --> 01:27:05,442
I was confused about the resolution.

1064
01:27:05,622 --> 01:27:06,824
Where did they come from?

1065
01:27:07,304 --> 01:27:09,847
Who did they speak to?

1066
01:27:09,867 --> 01:27:11,428
I was really confused.

1067
01:27:11,488 --> 01:27:16,133
And I just want to set it clear that the school committee did not have any meetings.

1068
01:27:16,473 --> 01:27:18,675
We were not talking about raising our salary.

1069
01:27:19,096 --> 01:27:20,977
And I'm talking from my own personal opinion.

1070
01:27:21,017 --> 01:27:22,098
Nobody's reached out to me.

1071
01:27:22,839 --> 01:27:24,300
It was not a thought in my mind.

1072
01:27:24,320 --> 01:27:30,022
I was surprised and confused and disheartened by the resolution.

1073
01:27:30,042 --> 01:27:33,664
It was just something that we're not expecting.

1074
01:27:33,884 --> 01:27:38,306
And I did hear, I got into the meeting late, but I did hear

1075
01:27:39,326 --> 01:27:46,850
Rick Caviello, Councilor Caviello mentioned that a pay cut in their salaries to make the salaries equal.

1076
01:27:47,190 --> 01:27:57,997
You know, I think that would be the best way to make the salaries equal across the two different, you know, boards between the school committee and the city council.

1077
01:27:58,517 --> 01:28:06,381
If there's going to be any changes, then maybe a decrease in the salary to bring the councilor salary back down to the school committee salary.

1078
01:28:07,822 --> 01:28:24,227
Okay, so I got my point across and I wasn't prepared and ready to speak, but I just hope that I made it clear that I object to this resolution and I hope and I pray that it does not pass tonight.

1079
01:28:24,907 --> 01:28:26,308
And thank you for your time.

1080
01:28:26,488 --> 01:28:27,248
Thank you, everybody.

1081
01:28:27,268 --> 01:28:29,949
Thank you, Kathy.

1082
01:28:29,989 --> 01:28:30,809
Thank you for speaking.

1083
01:28:31,449 --> 01:28:32,450
Just one second.

1084
01:28:33,070 --> 01:28:34,190
Kathy brings up a good point.

1085
01:28:34,230 --> 01:28:36,111
People may have come into the room or joined.

1086
01:28:36,596 --> 01:28:37,757
since the motions were made.

1087
01:28:37,797 --> 01:28:42,779
But the current motion on the floor is amendments from President Morrell and Councilor Knight.

1088
01:28:42,859 --> 01:28:44,440
Councilor Knight's for some legal questions.

1089
01:28:44,900 --> 01:28:57,007
President Morrell has amended to strike some sentences around the majority makeup of the bodies as well as has suggested that future committee of the whole look at a phase in or or a change to this proposal.

1090
01:28:57,367 --> 01:28:58,827
So that is what is currently up for.

1091
01:28:59,028 --> 01:29:01,549
That is the motion currently on the floor is to send this to committee of the whole

1092
01:29:02,029 --> 01:29:03,770
for more discussion with those amendments.

1093
01:29:03,830 --> 01:29:05,951
And with that, I will go back to the podium.

1094
01:29:06,572 --> 01:29:06,872
Thank you.

1095
01:29:06,892 --> 01:29:07,852
Name and address for the record.

1096
01:29:08,193 --> 01:29:10,854
Hi, Melanie North, 45 Cross Street.

1097
01:29:11,815 --> 01:29:13,195
Good evening, City Council.

1098
01:29:13,596 --> 01:29:18,939
I'm speaking as an employee, taxpayer, and parent of Medford and Medford Public Schools.

1099
01:29:19,619 --> 01:29:25,983
I am beyond insulted about this proposed raise that President Morrell and any other council member is voting for.

1100
01:29:26,963 --> 01:29:33,545
I feel that it is an abuse of power and pure negligence to even consider this preposterous raise.

1101
01:29:34,265 --> 01:29:37,847
As an employee, we were told that there was just no money in the budget.

1102
01:29:38,247 --> 01:29:44,329
In fact, Dr. Cushing just stated last week to McGlynn in a meeting that the budget is the tightest it's ever been.

1103
01:29:45,109 --> 01:29:51,855
There has also been talk of eliminating even more positions and more layoffs in the next school year due to budget constraints.

1104
01:29:52,175 --> 01:29:58,300
However, on the heels of winning the election for many of you and the mayor, you have conveniently located $117,000 in the budget.

1105
01:30:00,962 --> 01:30:07,124
The paraprofessionals were told that although we were invaluable, the school committee was not able to provide a livable wage.

1106
01:30:07,665 --> 01:30:21,090
If this 140% raise were to go through, the school committee members would be making more than our most qualified kindergarten aides and classroom assistants that work tirelessly year after year with multiple jobs to survive.

1107
01:30:21,590 --> 01:30:25,671
We work an average of 1,300 hours and more each school year.

1108
01:30:25,991 --> 01:30:29,753
Most, if not all, overtime is unpaid due to budget cuts.

1109
01:30:30,373 --> 01:30:39,997
There, this is also being proposed as a general equity issue where the school committee has been dominated by females, which historically has mostly been men.

1110
01:30:40,577 --> 01:30:43,458
We have held, that have held the school committee positions.

1111
01:30:43,679 --> 01:30:47,160
However, paraprofessionals are by far female dominated.

1112
01:30:47,240 --> 01:30:49,421
So shouldn't we be considered for 140% race?

1113
01:30:55,177 --> 01:31:00,559
If you're making this about inequality, we clearly have some work to do on the negotiation table.

1114
01:31:01,080 --> 01:31:05,301
Medford is the highest paid school committee in all of our surrounding areas.

1115
01:31:05,522 --> 01:31:07,602
I've done the research.

1116
01:31:07,983 --> 01:31:13,965
But we were told that there is no money from the very school committee that you're planning to give this raise to.

1117
01:31:14,445 --> 01:31:24,290
It seems quite coincidental that suddenly money is appearing to benefit them and not the employees in the trenches every day working with the students to prepare them for the future.

1118
01:31:24,870 --> 01:31:33,676
If you want to entice people to run, it should be so they can be part of making our district the best it can be, not because of the wages that we are going to receive.

1119
01:31:34,337 --> 01:31:36,618
You do not run for office to get rich.

1120
01:31:36,838 --> 01:31:38,700
You run for office to make a difference.

1121
01:31:39,620 --> 01:31:44,584
Medford Public is also actively trying to recruit paraprofessionals every single week.

1122
01:31:44,964 --> 01:31:49,107
Who would want to work in a district that will support political roles and not employees?

1123
01:31:49,687 --> 01:31:52,508
We have so many other issues that surround this raise.

1124
01:31:52,889 --> 01:32:00,032
How about our custodial staff that works tirelessly, even through COVID when everyone else was home, they still don't have a contract.

1125
01:32:00,433 --> 01:32:03,454
What about the police department that serve and protect our community?

1126
01:32:03,474 --> 01:32:09,898
I believe we should be working on getting both contracts done before anything should be discussed about the school committee.

1127
01:32:10,378 --> 01:32:11,819
I'm on the front lines each day.

1128
01:32:11,839 --> 01:32:16,301
I've been punched in the face, which has resulted in a black eye from a student.

1129
01:32:16,721 --> 01:32:18,262
I've been pushed, scratched,

1130
01:32:18,422 --> 01:32:21,044
and I get verbally abused each and every day.

1131
01:32:21,524 --> 01:32:23,825
I worked for a prison for almost two decades.

1132
01:32:24,186 --> 01:32:29,629
I've never been struck by an inmate or dealt with the stuff that I deal with on a daily basis.

1133
01:32:30,069 --> 01:32:31,110
That says something.

1134
01:32:31,130 --> 01:32:44,378
A grievance was put in since last year to be paid for the coverage that I thought I'd been told there's no budget to pay this, yet I show up to work each and every day with our most at-risk students.

1135
01:32:44,599 --> 01:32:44,839
Why?

1136
01:32:45,299 --> 01:32:46,260
because I love what I do.

1137
01:32:46,280 --> 01:32:57,749
I'm heavily involved in after school programs that I personally run, not because I'm offered money, but because I believe that students should be given the opportunity to succeed in all areas of life.

1138
01:32:58,369 --> 01:33:02,052
As a parent, taxpayer, and an employee, this rate is

1139
01:33:02,452 --> 01:33:04,073
This raise outrages me.

1140
01:33:04,454 --> 01:33:13,441
Considering our schools are bursting at the seams, McGlynn Elementary is pouring water in kindergarten classrooms every time it rains or snows for the last few years.

1141
01:33:14,042 --> 01:33:20,848
When outraged parents demanded this be fixed due to mold issues, we were told it's the flashing, just not in the budget to fix.

1142
01:33:21,488 --> 01:33:24,930
We need a new high school, and the list continues to grow.

1143
01:33:25,291 --> 01:33:34,357
Yet, Medford Public Schools pays so poorly that potential employees who would excel in our schools and be amazing teachers and or paras go to other districts.

1144
01:33:34,857 --> 01:33:43,763
It's really heartbreaking that the City Council does not see the need for proper staff and better wages over raising the school committee's raises.

1145
01:33:44,243 --> 01:33:46,465
The numbers don't lie, it's in black and white.

1146
01:33:46,825 --> 01:33:51,028
This does not seem like the fiscal responsibility that Sissy Hall preaches about.

1147
01:33:51,608 --> 01:33:58,292
My direct question to you is, the 2004 budget has already been approved for $179 million.

1148
01:33:58,433 --> 01:33:59,953
I do my research.

1149
01:34:00,574 --> 01:34:05,797
Can you tell me what line item will be reduced in the school's budget to compensate for these new raises?

1150
01:34:06,978 --> 01:34:07,578
Thank you for your time.

1151
01:34:07,598 --> 01:34:13,442
I'm going to go to Zoom.

1152
01:34:13,562 --> 01:34:16,304
I have Rebecca on Zoom.

1153
01:34:16,324 --> 01:34:18,846
Give us one second, Rebecca, and then name and address for the record.

1154
01:34:19,306 --> 01:34:20,507
Please try to respect the time.

1155
01:34:20,567 --> 01:34:20,867
Thank you.

1156
01:34:23,308 --> 01:34:26,209
Rebecca Davidson, 101 Yeoman's Ave.

1157
01:34:27,569 --> 01:34:28,450
Good evening, everyone.

1158
01:34:28,550 --> 01:34:31,771
I support the fact that this proposal is being presented this evening.

1159
01:34:32,011 --> 01:34:39,493
It's really important that we have socioeconomic diversity on our elected bodies so that these bodies fully reflect our city.

1160
01:34:40,154 --> 01:34:42,054
No one is running for the salary.

1161
01:34:42,334 --> 01:34:50,077
However, not being paid adequately for your time will absolutely constitute a barrier to running for those who are struggling to make ends meet.

1162
01:34:51,343 --> 01:34:55,725
This is a barrier not just on school committee, but in government participation in general.

1163
01:34:56,185 --> 01:34:58,486
So I appreciate the spirit behind this proposal.

1164
01:34:59,266 --> 01:35:07,769
I'm a parent of two kids in Medford, and as many have said, the current pay that our dedicated, hardworking Medford public school staff is nowhere near adequate.

1165
01:35:08,129 --> 01:35:12,131
And I wanna thank the teachers that have spoken this evening and highlighted their service to the city.

1166
01:35:12,731 --> 01:35:18,074
This has been an opportunity to hear about and spotlight additional equity issues our city is facing.

1167
01:35:18,514 --> 01:35:25,138
And from what I'm understanding tonight, there's no way for this body to direct funding to increase pay for MPS staff.

1168
01:35:25,579 --> 01:35:27,420
That would have to go through different mechanisms.

1169
01:35:28,160 --> 01:35:34,464
But the intent behind this proposal signals strong support for pay equity within Medford public schools as well.

1170
01:35:35,005 --> 01:35:41,309
And my hope is that we can move this conversation to a place where our budget reflects the need to increase salaries.

1171
01:35:41,809 --> 01:35:46,533
And for that, we need to be able to explore thoughtful ways of bringing additional revenue to the city.

1172
01:35:47,133 --> 01:35:59,159
Thank you for bringing this proposal to the table as an opportunity to raise awareness of multiple inequities facing our city, resulting from inadequate funding, so that we can move forward to make the city a better place for everyone.

1173
01:36:02,820 --> 01:36:03,581
Thank you, Rebecca.

1174
01:36:03,981 --> 01:36:07,242
I'm going to go to Anna on the podium.

1175
01:36:07,302 --> 01:36:08,683
Just name and address for the record, please.

1176
01:36:08,803 --> 01:36:09,103
Thank you.

1177
01:36:09,463 --> 01:36:11,444
Hannah Silberman, 15 Maynard Street.

1178
01:36:13,045 --> 01:36:13,225
Go ahead.

1179
01:36:13,663 --> 01:36:18,850
All right, my name is Hannah, and I work at the second largest school in Medford.

1180
01:36:18,970 --> 01:36:20,912
That's the Roberts Elementary School.

1181
01:36:20,932 --> 01:36:27,681
It goes Medford High School, Roberts Elementary School, and then I think the Brooks after that, and then the middle schools.

1182
01:36:28,182 --> 01:36:30,284
So we need to make that make a little more sense.

1183
01:36:31,365 --> 01:36:34,688
I think we should talk about rezoning before anyone talks about getting a raise.

1184
01:36:35,269 --> 01:36:38,131
At the Roberts, we have 576 students.

1185
01:36:38,351 --> 01:36:41,174
We're running out of physical space to contain them.

1186
01:36:42,395 --> 01:36:49,580
576 students, and yet we have the same amount of support staff as the other elementary schools, and some of which are half the size.

1187
01:36:49,961 --> 01:36:54,484
We're down to a skeleton crew, and administration continues to fatten up on school funding.

1188
01:36:55,285 --> 01:37:05,815
All we ever hear as teachers is that there isn't enough money, not enough to hire more classroom aides or to pay them more, not enough to raise our substitute pay, not enough money for paper even.

1189
01:37:05,835 --> 01:37:10,379
ESSER funds are running out, and those funds pay for over 30 people's salaries.

1190
01:37:10,900 --> 01:37:12,561
And what's going to happen to their jobs next year?

1191
01:37:12,982 --> 01:37:18,787
We've been told drastic cuts no need to be made, and adding these substantial raises is only going to make that worse.

1192
01:37:19,568 --> 01:37:23,371
And you aren't going to find any teachers here who disagree with you about equal pay for equal work.

1193
01:37:23,851 --> 01:37:28,895
This is a profession that's underpaid because it has historically been the work of women, as you said, President Morrell.

1194
01:37:29,815 --> 01:37:40,223
And yet, instead of correcting this, Medford is continuing to do what Medford has always done, spending school funding not on the people doing the physical, emotional, and mental labor of supporting our students,

1195
01:37:41,564 --> 01:37:44,508
but instead spending the money on those who are already in power.

1196
01:37:45,309 --> 01:37:50,897
We're talking about paying the school committee the same amount or more as our classroom aides for a part-time political job.

1197
01:37:51,397 --> 01:37:56,544
School committee stipend pay should be proportional to the pay of the people doing the work face-to-face with those students.

1198
01:37:57,225 --> 01:38:00,447
If you want to show that you care about equity, this is not the way to do it.

1199
01:38:00,907 --> 01:38:07,750
Counselor Collins counselor saying you said that this is not a zero sum game but then you need to show us, because so far this is all we see.

1200
01:38:08,171 --> 01:38:13,633
And that's what we're talking about here tonight, the funding of upper administration, while the students and the staff are drowning.

1201
01:38:14,194 --> 01:38:16,155
We need to prioritize the schools themselves.

1202
01:38:17,415 --> 01:38:20,057
Please do the right thing and spend school funds.

1203
01:38:21,437 --> 01:38:22,737
on what's really important.

1204
01:38:22,837 --> 01:38:25,838
We need to fix our buildings and increase substitute pay.

1205
01:38:26,258 --> 01:38:29,619
We need more aides, more social workers, more SPED and Yale staff.

1206
01:38:29,659 --> 01:38:33,180
We do not need to spend even more money on upper administration.

1207
01:38:33,200 --> 01:38:33,921
Thank you.

1208
01:38:33,941 --> 01:38:42,783
Thank you Hannah.

1209
01:38:42,803 --> 01:38:49,165
My name is Anthony Guillaume and between this meeting and the healthcare negotiations tomorrow, I live here today.

1210
01:38:53,174 --> 01:39:07,801
I am the president of the Medford Teachers Association, and I appreciate the call for civil conversation, but my member's anger is real, it is palpable, and we're being antagonized into this anger by this proposal.

1211
01:39:09,242 --> 01:39:16,505
We're being antagonized because every day we walk into the schools, and we hear that amount of money is available, and we see where it can go.

1212
01:39:17,105 --> 01:39:22,128
We see a lack of substitutes, we see a lack of aids, we see a leaking roof,

1213
01:39:23,345 --> 01:39:29,150
And then we hear that the school committee is our bridge, is our connection to the city.

1214
01:39:30,812 --> 01:39:34,535
We passed a vote of no confidence not a year ago.

1215
01:39:35,216 --> 01:39:39,339
96% of us said we do not have the confidence in the school committee during contract negotiations.

1216
01:39:39,820 --> 01:39:41,581
That has never been rescinded.

1217
01:39:42,382 --> 01:39:44,044
We never said, oh, okay, it's good now.

1218
01:39:44,784 --> 01:39:46,446
And yet we're being told this is all connected.

1219
01:39:46,466 --> 01:39:47,367
This isn't a zero sum.

1220
01:39:49,136 --> 01:39:51,218
Well, I can appreciate the call for civility.

1221
01:39:51,558 --> 01:39:53,400
The anger is real and that has to be recognized.

1222
01:39:53,420 --> 01:39:58,184
I want to talk about some part-time jobs if we're talking about part-time job pay.

1223
01:39:59,705 --> 01:40:07,972
I want to talk about, first, our football coach, who's been celebrated all this year producing Massachusetts athletes of the week.

1224
01:40:09,213 --> 01:40:15,238
That coach has paid $3,000 to $6,000 less than all the surrounding cities, and even that is comparable to Medford.

1225
01:40:16,289 --> 01:40:20,030
Our soccer coach, $2,000 to $3,000 less.

1226
01:40:20,290 --> 01:40:22,131
Our hockey coach, $2,000 to $3,000 less.

1227
01:40:22,231 --> 01:40:24,371
Our basketball coach, $2,000 to $3,000 less.

1228
01:40:25,412 --> 01:40:27,952
Move out of athletics, move into the school.

1229
01:40:28,712 --> 01:40:40,956
Our Gay-Straight Alliance advisor, who makes our LGBTQIA plus students not only feel welcome, but celebrated in our schools, gets $600 to put on dances, to organize protests, to speak at rallies.

1230
01:40:42,580 --> 01:40:55,362
Our senior class advisor, who puts on prom, who does fundraising, who works with the class, gets $1,000 for the year, which is an increase from when they're the freshman class advisor, and they get $600.

1231
01:40:58,595 --> 01:41:12,844
The advisor to our Black Student Union who puts on our celebrated Haitian, who helps, I should say, the students do most of it, as they have said, but supervises our Haitian Flag Day and our Black History Month assembly, no compensation, does it out of the goodness of his heart.

1232
01:41:15,186 --> 01:41:19,408
We're all doing part-time jobs to make it work.

1233
01:41:20,869 --> 01:41:23,651
And some of us don't have the option to step away from our part-time jobs.

1234
01:41:23,891 --> 01:41:27,774
It's not a matter of something we'd like to do, it's something we have to do to survive.

1235
01:41:29,929 --> 01:41:37,753
So I ask now that this money that is available by whatever means necessary be moved back into the schools.

1236
01:41:38,693 --> 01:41:44,516
I ask that we enter this new year on a platform of transparency and trust and not of nepotism and top-down priorities.

1237
01:41:45,217 --> 01:41:48,778
I ask that we come to work in a city that believes and cares about us.

1238
01:41:49,779 --> 01:41:50,860
And I thank you all for your time.

1239
01:41:50,880 --> 01:41:54,862
Thank you.

1240
01:42:03,100 --> 01:42:04,961
I'm going to go to President Morrell, and then back to the podium.

1241
01:42:04,981 --> 01:42:05,521
President Morrell.

1242
01:42:05,581 --> 01:42:06,841
I just have a brief point of information.

1243
01:42:06,861 --> 01:42:10,462
I just want to note that no money has been moved anywhere just at this point.

1244
01:42:10,502 --> 01:42:11,343
No vote has been taken.

1245
01:42:11,363 --> 01:42:15,624
I just want to make sure that's clear, because I understand the intent of what you said.

1246
01:42:15,664 --> 01:42:18,265
I just want to make sure that's clear, because that happened.

1247
01:42:18,285 --> 01:42:18,985
Thank you, Madam President.

1248
01:42:19,825 --> 01:42:20,966
Name and address for the record, please.

1249
01:42:21,286 --> 01:42:22,426
My name's, can you hear me?

1250
01:42:22,446 --> 01:42:23,507
My name's Joanna McKay.

1251
01:42:24,147 --> 01:42:26,528
I'm a teacher at the Roberts Elementary, so I'll give 35 Court Street.

1252
01:42:28,427 --> 01:42:29,587
So I'm a fourth grade teacher.

1253
01:42:29,607 --> 01:42:32,568
I'm a member of the Teachers Association.

1254
01:42:32,608 --> 01:42:34,008
I was on the negotiating team.

1255
01:42:34,589 --> 01:42:37,429
So I understand some of what you go to, to an extent.

1256
01:42:37,809 --> 01:42:44,151
Like many people tonight, I'm here because the extent of this raise being proposed confuses me.

1257
01:42:44,791 --> 01:42:45,572
It disheartens me.

1258
01:42:45,872 --> 01:42:47,152
Quite frankly, it disgusts me.

1259
01:42:48,198 --> 01:42:50,359
I'm not here to argue whether or not they need a raise.

1260
01:42:50,519 --> 01:42:51,460
Everyone should get a raise.

1261
01:42:51,860 --> 01:42:52,860
That's a whole different point.

1262
01:42:53,280 --> 01:42:57,482
I don't understand the level of this raise and the context in which it came about.

1263
01:42:58,062 --> 01:43:03,585
From speaking to many people on seeing comments on social media, it's evident that people don't agree with this.

1264
01:43:04,405 --> 01:43:05,506
It's too much of a raise.

1265
01:43:06,666 --> 01:43:14,870
And the idea that it has to do with equity and parity and diversity is ironic to me, as what you heard everyone saying.

1266
01:43:15,390 --> 01:43:15,870
I don't get it.

1267
01:43:17,782 --> 01:43:19,750
I reached out to Nicole Morel.

1268
01:43:19,830 --> 01:43:21,275
